# .zap/rules.tsv — seeded by slopstopper install.sh.
#
# OWASP ZAP rule overrides for the DAST scan. Two common false positives
# for content-heavy sites ship commented-out below. Uncomment ONLY the
# rules that apply to your site, and keep the `# why` line so the
# exception is documented at the point of suppression.
#
# Format: <plugin-id>\tIGNORE\t# why this is accepted on this site
# See https://www.zaproxy.org/docs/alerts/ for the plugin registry.
#
# Honoured by slopstopper's dast:analyze task AND by the DAST gate
# (.ss/scripts/check-dast-alerts.py).

# 90003	IGNORE	# SRI: GTM script and similar cross-domain scripts are
#                # rotated by the third party; no stable SRI hash is viable

# 10099	IGNORE	# Source Code Disclosure - SQL: false positive on tutorial
#                # blog posts containing SQL code blocks (Databricks/Spark/
#                # Cosmos emulator). ZAP's heuristic matches SQL syntax in
#                # <pre><code> blocks as if the application were leaking
#                # source code; it isn't
